The suspect was shot in the head during the exchange and is now under police guard in hospital. JOHANNESBURG Officers have shot and wounded a suspected hijacker who allegedly tried to steal a marked police car in the south of Johannesburg.Police say they arrested the suspect following a high-speed chase and a shootout.The alleged hijacker lost control of the vehicle and drove into a pole.He was shot in the head during the exchange and is under police guard in hospital.Spokesman Lungelo Dlamini said: While police were looking for the car it was spotted in Alberton, then a shootout ensued. 